<div id="post-1467" class="cf post-1467 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2007/03/my-own-private-icann/" title="My Own Private ICANN?" rel="bookmark">My Own Private ICANN?</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Mar</p>
			<p class="post-day">28</p>
			<p class="post-year">2007</p>				
		</div>

		Susan Crawford reports that ICANN is discussing the possibility of becoming a &#8220;private international organization.&#8221; I&#8217;m not sure exactly what that means, or whether it&#8217;s a good thing. But it could be significant. ICANN has many problems, but it&#8217;s a lynchpin holding the Internet as we know it together.
		
	</div>

